item.title: CVE-2023-26150|2023-10-03T05:00:02.176Z -- n%2Fa -- asyncua
item.description: Versions of the package asyncua before 0.9.96 are vulnerable to Improper Authentication such that it is possible to access Address Space without encryption and authentication. **Note:** This issue is a result of missing checks for services that require an active session.

item.title: CVE-2023-26151|2023-10-03T05:00:01.093Z -- n%2Fa -- asyncua
item.description: Versions of the package asyncua before 0.9.96 are vulnerable to Denial of Service (DoS) such that an attacker can send a malformed packet and as a result, the server will enter into an infinite loop and consume excessive memory.
